    "description": {
      "value": "<p>A blow from an aboleth's tentacle can cause a terrible affliction. A creature hit by a tentacle must succeed on a DC 19 Fortitude save or begin to transform over the next 1d4+1 minutes, the skin gradually becoming a clear, slimy membrane. An afflicted creature must remain moistened with cool, fresh water or take 1d12 points of damage every 10 minutes. The slime reduces the creature's natural armor bonus by 1 (but never to less than 0). The save DC is Constitution-based.</p>\n<div>\n<p>A <em>remove disease</em> spell cast before the transformation is complete will restore an afflicted creature to normal. Afterward, however, only a <em>heal</em> or <em>mass heal</em> spell can reverse the affliction.</p>\n</div>",
